<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-16"><hi rend="italic">July 16,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Summoned to-day by minister of state, who told me confidentially that
                            after the council of to-morrow he would be able to answer officially my
                            note of June 18, demanding payment of Mora indemnity, that the council
                            yesterday resolved to offer to satisfy said demand by payment of the
                            principal in three installments at the times indicated in your
                            conversation with Dupuy of the 21st June. While clearly expressing his
                            expectation to pay principal only, he declined to intimate whether he
                            proposed to tender gold or depreciated Spanish currency. What shall I
                            say on that point?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>